{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":496,"text":"Writing biography is a strange thing to do."},{"time":6216,"text":"It's a journey into the foreign territory"},{"time":8899,"text":"of somebody else's life,"},{"time":12095,"text":"a journey, an exploration that can take you places"},{"time":14768,"text":"you never dreamed of going"},{"time":17039,"text":"and still can't quite believe you've been,"},{"time":19264,"text":"especially if, like me, you're an agnostic Jew"},{"time":22992,"text":"and the life you've been exploring"},{"time":24817,"text":"is that of Muhammad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29649,"text":"Five years ago, for instance,"},{"time":32080,"text":"I found myself waking each morning in misty Seattle"},{"time":35348,"text":"to what I knew was an impossible question:"},{"time":38831,"text":"What actually happened"},{"time":42049,"text":"one desert night,"},{"time":43488,"text":"half the world and almost half of history away?"},{"time":47082,"text":"What happened, that is,"},{"time":48802,"text":"on the night in the year 610"},{"time":51120,"text":"when Muhammad received the first revelation of the Koran"},{"time":54971,"text":"on a mountain just outside Mecca?"},{"time":59048,"text":"This is the core mystical moment of Islam,"},{"time":63653,"text":"and as such, of course,"},{"time":65019,"text":"it defies empirical analysis."},{"time":68095,"text":"Yet the question wouldn't let go of me."},{"time":72200,"text":"I was fully aware that for someone as secular as I am,"},{"time":75384,"text":"just asking it could be seen"},{"time":77263,"text":"as pure chutzpah."},{"time":80523,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":83205,"text":"And I plead guilty as charged,"},{"time":85816,"text":"because all exploration, physical or intellectual,"},{"time":89847,"text":"is inevitably in some sense an act of transgression,"},{"time":93724,"text":"of crossing boundaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97121,"text":"Still, some boundaries are larger than others."},{"time":103136,"text":"So a human encountering the divine,"},{"time":106056,"text":"as Muslims believe Muhammad did,"},{"time":109178,"text":"to the rationalist, this is a matter not of fact"},{"time":112019,"text":"but of wishful fiction,"},{"time":113776,"text":"and like all of us, I like to think of myself as rational."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117714,"text":"Which might be why when I looked at the earliest accounts"},{"time":120598,"text":"we have of that night,"},{"time":122375,"text":"what struck me even more than what happened"},{"time":125194,"text":"was what did not happen."},{"time":130716,"text":"Muhammad did not come floating off the mountain"},{"time":133868,"text":"as though walking on air."},{"time":136818,"text":"He did not run down shouting, \"Hallelujah!\""},{"time":139292,"text":"and \"Bless the Lord!\""},{"time":141652,"text":"He did not radiate light and joy."},{"time":145380,"text":"There were no choirs of angels,"},{"time":146959,"text":"no music of the spheres, no elation, no ecstasy,"},{"time":150259,"text":"no golden aura surrounding him,"},{"time":153921,"text":"no sense of an absolute, fore-ordained role"},{"time":158063,"text":"as the messenger of God."},{"time":161139,"text":"That is, he did none of the things"},{"time":164094,"text":"that might make it easy to cry foul,"},{"time":166848,"text":"to put down the whole story as a pious fable."},{"time":171995,"text":"Quite the contrary."},{"time":174827,"text":"In his own reported words,"},{"time":178572,"text":"he was convinced at first"},{"time":180949,"text":"that what had happened couldn't have been real."},{"time":186230,"text":"At best, he thought, it had to have been a hallucination --"},{"time":188942,"text":"a trick of the eye or the ear, perhaps,"},{"time":190751,"text":"or his own mind working against him."},{"time":192926,"text":"At worst, possession --"},{"time":195103,"text":"that he'd been seized by an evil jinn,"},{"time":197392,"text":"a spirit out to deceive him,"},{"time":199183,"text":"even to crush the life out of him."},{"time":202192,"text":"In fact, he was so sure that he could only be majnun,"},{"time":205216,"text":"possessed by a jinn,"},{"time":206844,"text":"that when he found himself still alive,"},{"time":208956,"text":"his first impulse was to finish the job himself,"},{"time":213805,"text":"to leap off the highest cliff"},{"time":216008,"text":"and escape the terror of what he'd experienced"},{"time":220126,"text":"by putting an end to all experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227228,"text":"So the man who fled down the mountain that night"},{"time":230148,"text":"trembled not with joy"},{"time":232599,"text":"but with a stark, primordial fear."},{"time":237319,"text":"He was overwhelmed not with conviction, but by doubt."},{"time":243239,"text":"And that panicked disorientation,"},{"time":246040,"text":"that sundering of everything familiar,"},{"time":248919,"text":"that daunting awareness of something"},{"time":252603,"text":"beyond human comprehension,"},{"time":255512,"text":"can only be called a terrible awe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262087,"text":"This might be somewhat difficult to grasp"},{"time":265301,"text":"now that we use the word \"awesome\""},{"time":267839,"text":"to describe a new app or a viral video."},{"time":272018,"text":"With the exception perhaps of a massive earthquake,"},{"time":275223,"text":"we're protected from real awe."},{"time":277871,"text":"We close the doors and hunker down,"},{"time":279759,"text":"convinced that we're in control,"},{"time":282305,"text":"or, at least, hoping for control."},{"time":285327,"text":"We do our best to ignore the fact that"},{"time":287235,"text":"we don't always have it,"},{"time":289296,"text":"and that not everything can be explained."},{"time":292053,"text":"Yet whether you're a rationalist or a mystic,"},{"time":296215,"text":"whether you think the words Muhammad heard that night"},{"time":298910,"text":"came from inside himself or from outside,"},{"time":303174,"text":"what's clear is that he did experience them,"},{"time":307878,"text":"and that he did so with a force that would shatter"},{"time":310314,"text":"his sense of himself and his world"},{"time":312635,"text":"and transform this otherwise modest man"},{"time":315775,"text":"into a radical advocate for social and economic justice."},{"time":322468,"text":"Fear was the only sane response,"},{"time":327710,"text":"the only human response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332734,"text":"Too human for some,"},{"time":335242,"text":"like conservative Muslim theologians who maintain that"},{"time":337975,"text":"the account of his wanting to kill himself"},{"time":339842,"text":"shouldn't even be mentioned, despite the fact"},{"time":342280,"text":"that it's in the earliest Islamic biographies."},{"time":346734,"text":"They insist that he never doubted"},{"time":349525,"text":"for even a single moment, let alone despaired."},{"time":356135,"text":"Demanding perfection, they refuse to tolerate"},{"time":359972,"text":"human imperfection."},{"time":364691,"text":"Yet what, exactly, is imperfect about doubt?"},{"time":371886,"text":"As I read those early accounts, I realized it was"},{"time":374860,"text":"precisely Muhammad's doubt that brought him alive for me,"},{"time":378670,"text":"that allowed me to begin to see him in full,"},{"time":381067,"text":"to accord him the integrity of reality."},{"time":384653,"text":"And the more I thought about it,"},{"time":386822,"text":"the more it made sense that he doubted,"},{"time":389839,"text":"because doubt is essential to faith."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396422,"text":"If this seems a startling idea at first,"},{"time":399302,"text":"consider that doubt, as Graham Greene once put it,"},{"time":402963,"text":"is the heart of the matter."},{"time":406798,"text":"Abolish all doubt, and what's left is not faith,"},{"time":411203,"text":"but absolute, heartless conviction."},{"time":416446,"text":"You're certain that you possess the Truth --"},{"time":420317,"text":"inevitably offered with an implied uppercase T --"},{"time":424608,"text":"and this certainty quickly devolves"},{"time":427166,"text":"into dogmatism and righteousness,"},{"time":430678,"text":"by which I mean a demonstrative, overweening pride"},{"time":434781,"text":"in being so very right,"},{"time":438569,"text":"in short, the arrogance of fundamentalism."},{"time":446457,"text":"It has to be one of the multiple ironies of history"},{"time":450933,"text":"that a favorite expletive of Muslim fundamentalists"},{"time":453991,"text":"is the same one once used by the Christian fundamentalists"},{"time":457182,"text":"known as Crusaders:"},{"time":459994,"text":"\"infidel,\" from the Latin for \"faithless.\""},{"time":465219,"text":"Doubly ironic, in this case, because their absolutism"},{"time":469558,"text":"is in fact the opposite of faith."},{"time":474023,"text":"In effect, they are the infidels."},{"time":479982,"text":"Like fundamentalists of all religious stripes,"},{"time":482809,"text":"they have no questions, only answers."},{"time":486654,"text":"They found the perfect antidote to thought"},{"time":489446,"text":"and the ideal refuge of the hard demands of real faith."},{"time":493217,"text":"They don't have to struggle for it like Jacob"},{"time":495166,"text":"wrestling through the night with the angel,"},{"time":497216,"text":"or like Jesus in his 40 days and nights in the wilderness,"},{"time":500374,"text":"or like Muhammad, not only that night on the mountain,"},{"time":503576,"text":"but throughout his years as a prophet,"},{"time":506070,"text":"with the Koran constantly urging him not to despair,"},{"time":510254,"text":"and condemning those who most loudly proclaim"},{"time":513542,"text":"that they know everything there is to know"},{"time":517339,"text":"and that they and they alone are right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524233,"text":"And yet we, the vast and still far too silent majority,"},{"time":531646,"text":"have ceded the public arena to this extremist minority."},{"time":537415,"text":"We've allowed Judaism to be claimed"},{"time":539908,"text":"by violently messianic West Bank settlers,"},{"time":543779,"text":"Christianity by homophobic hypocrites"},{"time":546726,"text":"and misogynistic bigots,"},{"time":549246,"text":"Islam by suicide bombers."},{"time":554205,"text":"And we've allowed ourselves to be blinded to the fact that"},{"time":556976,"text":"no matter whether they claim to be Christians,"},{"time":559168,"text":"Jews or Muslims,"},{"time":560783,"text":"militant extremists are none of the above."},{"time":566438,"text":"They're a cult all their own, blood brothers"},{"time":572052,"text":"steeped in other people's blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577546,"text":"This isn't faith."},{"time":579748,"text":"It's fanaticism, and we have to stop confusing the two."},{"time":584910,"text":"We have to recognize that real faith has no easy answers."},{"time":589932,"text":"It's difficult and stubborn."},{"time":594010,"text":"It involves an ongoing struggle,"},{"time":596248,"text":"a continual questioning of what we think we know,"},{"time":599302,"text":"a wrestling with issues and ideas."},{"time":601867,"text":"It goes hand in hand with doubt,"},{"time":605167,"text":"in a never-ending conversation with it,"},{"time":608244,"text":"and sometimes in conscious defiance of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614639,"text":"And this conscious defiance is why I, as an agnostic,"},{"time":619687,"text":"can still have faith."},{"time":623828,"text":"I have faith, for instance, that peace in the Middle East"},{"time":626816,"text":"is possible despite the ever-accumulating mass of evidence"},{"time":631126,"text":"to the contrary."},{"time":634287,"text":"I'm not convinced of this."},{"time":636659,"text":"I can hardly say I believe it."},{"time":638783,"text":"I can only have faith in it,"},{"time":640725,"text":"commit myself, that is, to the idea of it,"},{"time":644743,"text":"and I do this precisely because of the temptation"},{"time":647744,"text":"to throw up my hands in resignation"},{"time":649744,"text":"and retreat into silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653265,"text":"Because despair is self-fulfilling."},{"time":657946,"text":"If we call something impossible,"},{"time":660266,"text":"we act in such a way that we make it so."},{"time":664034,"text":"And I, for one, refuse to live that way."},{"time":669967,"text":"In fact, most of us do,"},{"time":672266,"text":"whether we're atheist or theist"},{"time":675842,"text":"or anywhere in between or beyond, for that matter,"},{"time":679782,"text":"what drives us is that, despite our doubts"},{"time":684098,"text":"and even because of our doubts,"},{"time":686426,"text":"we reject the nihilism of despair."},{"time":690898,"text":"We insist on faith in the future"},{"time":694131,"text":"and in each other."},{"time":698869,"text":"Call this naive if you like."},{"time":702370,"text":"Call it impossibly idealistic if you must."},{"time":705467,"text":"But one thing is sure:"},{"time":707895,"text":"Call it human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711361,"text":"Could Muhammad have so radically changed his world"},{"time":714396,"text":"without such faith, without the refusal"},{"time":717248,"text":"to cede to the arrogance of closed-minded certainty?"},{"time":721964,"text":"I think not."},{"time":725230,"text":"After keeping company with him as a writer"},{"time":727273,"text":"for the past five years, I can't see"},{"time":730573,"text":"that he'd be anything but utterly outraged"},{"time":735676,"text":"at the militant fundamentalists who claim to speak"},{"time":738823,"text":"and act in his name in the Middle East and elsewhere today."},{"time":744292,"text":"He'd be appalled at the repression of half the population"},{"time":748582,"text":"because of their gender."},{"time":751580,"text":"He'd be torn apart by the bitter divisiveness of sectarianism."},{"time":759561,"text":"He'd call out terrorism for what it is,"},{"time":762267,"text":"not only criminal but an obscene travesty"},{"time":767011,"text":"of everything he believed in and struggled for."},{"time":771916,"text":"He'd say what the Koran says: Anyone who takes a life"},{"time":777185,"text":"takes the life of all humanity."},{"time":780386,"text":"Anyone who saves a life, saves the life of all humanity."},{"time":787582,"text":"And he'd commit himself fully"},{"time":790652,"text":"to the hard and thorny process of making peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797672,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799107,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":803506,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}